CREATE TABLE students (
    id NUMBER PRIMARY KEY, 
    age NUMBER, 
    hobby VARCHAR(50),
    name VARCHAR(50)
);

Step 3: Storing Information (INSERT)
To put data into your newly created table, you use the INSERT INTO command. You specify the table, the columns you want to fill, and the values.

INSERT INTO students (id, age, hobby, name) 
VALUES (1, 18, 'Coding', 'Trishul');

INSERT INTO students (id, age, hobby, name) 
VALUES (2, 19, 'Robotics', 'Rahul');
